overview: The user initiated a request to enhance the aesthetic appeal of their
  sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too generic. The agent
  began by conducting a thorough review of the existing visual design,
  identifying areas for improvement in color palette, typography, spacing, form
  elements, and overall visual interest. A new, calming sleep-themed color
  palette was introduced, along with custom utility classes for gradients and
  shadows. The main form layout was redesigned with decorative background
  elements and an improved progress indicator. Key UI components like
  checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards received significant styling
  enhancements. All questionnaire sections were updated to ensure consistent
  theming and a more polished user experience. During this process, a console
  error related to null values being passed to input components was identified
  and fixed by modifying the base Input component to safely handle null values.
  The overall outcome was a visually cohesive, professional, and calming
  application that better reflects its purpose.
